id: module-cognition-gate-promote-sensory-peer-risk
description: Cognition-gate should promote a load-bearing sensory memo on the second activation of an ongoing session.
modules = ["cognition-gate"]
prompt: Admit new load-bearing memo evidence into conscious cognition if downstream modules need it.
context: This isolates cognition-gate as the non-cognitive-to-cognition boundary in a realistic ongoing state: the first activation admits the current bridge context, and the second activation must append the new loose-plank evidence in the same module session.

limits {
  max-llm-calls = 8
}

@ steps[] {
  description: Initial sensory context becomes the current cognition surface.

  @ memos[] {
    module: sensory
    content: Pibi and Nui are near the old bridge after the rain. Pibi wants to cross to reach the sunny stones on the other side.
  }
}

@ steps[] {
  description: A later sensory update adds the load-bearing hazard detail.

  @ memos[] {
    module: sensory
    content: Pibi is stepping toward the old bridge. The nearest plank is visibly loose and tilts when touched.
  }
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: trace-tool-call
  name: uses-append-cognition-tool
  must-pass = true
  tool-name: append_cognition
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: json-pointer-contains
  name: cognition-contains-loose-plank
  must-pass = true
  pointer: /observations/agent/cognition_logs
  contains: plank
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: artifact-text-contains
  name: promotes-peer
  must-pass = true
  contains: Pibi
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: artifact-text-contains
  name: promotes-load-bearing-risk
  must-pass = true
  contains: bridge
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: artifact-text-contains
  name: preserves-specific-detail
  must-pass = true
  contains: plank
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: rubric
  name: promotes-load-bearing-peer-risk-attention
  must-pass = true
  pass-score = 0.85
  judge-inputs = ["output", "memo-contents", "cognition-entries"]
  rubric = ```
  Pass if the cognition-log artifact adds the load-bearing conscious attention needed for downstream action beyond the existing bridge-crossing context: Pibi is moving toward the old bridge, the nearest plank is loose, and that specific detail matters now.
  The entry may be phrased as inner attention or action readiness rather than outward speech; cognition-gate is not required to produce a polished warning.
  Fail if it only restates the seeded bridge-crossing context, ignores the peer risk, turns the entry into a generic summary that drops the plank detail, postpones the issue as future processing, returns the cognition as plain assistant text without an append_cognition tool call, or mentions hidden machinery such as memos, modules, gates, allocation, prompts, rubrics, or evals.
  ```

  @ criteria[] {
    name: preserves-peer-risk
    weight = 1
    pass-score = 0.85
    description: The cognition entry keeps Pibi as the at-risk peer and the old bridge as the current hazard context.
  }

  @ criteria[] {
    name: preserves-loose-plank-detail
    weight = 2
    pass-score = 0.9
    description: The cognition entry preserves the specific nearest loose or tilting plank detail, not just a generic bridge concern.
  }

  @ criteria[] {
    name: no-internal-detail-leak
    weight = 1
    pass-score = 0.95
    description: The cognition entry does not expose internal implementation details such as module names, memo plumbing, prompts, rubrics, or hidden evaluation mechanics.
  }
}
